  "prompt": "My H1b visa is under Admin processing for about a year now, and there's has been no update so far. What options do I have?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about the delay in your H1B visa processing. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Contacting the Consulate or Embassy**: Reach out to the consulate or embassy where your application is being processed. You can inquire about the status of your application and ask for any updates.\n\n2. **Seeking Assistance from Your Employer**: Your employer might be able to provide support or inquire through their legal counsel or immigration specialist. They can sometimes expedite the process by contacting relevant authorities.\n\n3. **Congressional Inquiry**: Some applicants have found it helpful to contact their local congressional representative. They can sometimes intervene on your behalf to inquire about the status of your visa.\n\n4. **Legal Assistance**: Consulting with an immigration attorney can be beneficial. They can provide specific legal advice, help navigate the complexities of administrative processing, and potentially expedite the process.\n\n5. **USCIS Ombudsman**: You can reach out to the USCIS Ombudsman, whose office can sometimes assist in resolving long-pending cases.\n\n6. **Checking for Updates**: Regularly check the status of your application online through the Consular Electronic Application Center (CEAC) and the USCIS website.\n\n7. **Expedited Processing**: In some cases, there might be criteria for expedited processing due to emergencies or other compelling reasons. Your attorney can advise you on whether you qualify for this.\n\nRemember to maintain proper documentation and records of all communications and actions taken regarding your visa application.",
